mklab hands-off lab — local site overlay

This directory is copied over the upstream `preseed/local/` tree by
setup-hands-off.sh, replacing Philip Hands' own example site data (his
customers' hostnames/users) with the lab's.  It is the framework's intended
per-site customization hook — see the upstream `preseed/local/README`.

Contents:
  preseed   -- site-wide preseed pulled in by the _/core/locals class; here it
               makes the minimal default install unattended (accounts, disk pin,
               serial console).

To add site-specific classes / per-host overrides, follow the upstream layout
documented in preseed/local/README (local/_hostname/<fqdn>/…, local/_users/…,
local/partition/…). When you change anything here and are running WITH signature
checking, re-run `setup-hands-off.sh --sign` so the regenerated MD5SUMS covers it.
